From: y2k38-abi
Subject: [PATCH] rs6000/linux: define __Y2K38_ABI__ builtin macro (optional)

This is a SKETCH for ELDK-era GCC. It does not change time_t.
It only injects preprocessor defines so application code can
detect the toolchain flavor that ships y2k38 headers in sysroot.

Apply only if you rebuild ELDK GCC; preferred approach is still
sysroot headers + -specs without patching GCC.

---
 gcc/config/rs6000/linux.h | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/gcc/config/rs6000/linux.h b/gcc/config/rs6000/linux.h
index 0000000..1111111 100644
--- a/gcc/config/rs6000/linux.h
+++ b/gcc/config/rs6000/linux.h
@@ -/* existing LINUX_TARGET_OS_CPP_BUILTINS block — conceptual append */-
+#ifndef __Y2K38_ABI_TOOLCHAIN_SKETCH__
+#define __Y2K38_ABI_TOOLCHAIN_SKETCH__
+/* In a real patch, extend TARGET_OS_CPP_BUILTINS():
+ *   builtin_define ("__Y2K38_ABI__=1");
+ *   builtin_define_std ("__SIZEOF_Y2K38_TIME_T__=8");
+ * Prefer installing headers under $sysroot/usr/include/y2k38 instead.
+ */
+#endif
